The paper deals with the application of statistical methods to analyze language change in diachronic corpora, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses simulations and statistical tests, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of the approach and the need for caution in interpreting results, which is relevant to the subfield of social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses a big-data approach to linguistic research, which is also relevant to the subfield of data mining (cs.DL).
